    "The predicted vs actual plot shows the model tracks the true scores reasonably\n",
    "well, points cluster around the red diagonal line. The model does struggle\n",
    "slightly at the lower end of scores (students performing below ~60), where\n",
    "predictions are less accurate. This does make sense because low performers are\n",
    "underrepresented in this dataset (remember how Final_Score was a left-skewed \n",
    "distribution).\n",
    "\n",
    "The residuals are centered very close to 0 (mean = 0.19), which confirms\n",
    "there is no systematic bias in our predictions. The distribution approximates\n",
    "a bell curve, which is a good sign for the assumptions of linear regression.\n",
    "The spread (std = 6.61) means our predictions are off by about 6.6 points on \n",
    "either side, on average. This is equivalent to about 6-7% of the 100-point scale.\n",
    "\n",
    "Overall, the model explains about 73% of the variance in Final_Score (R²=0.73).\n",
    "Given that academic performance is influenced by many factors outside our\n",
    "dataset (test-day circumstances, prior subject knowledge, teaching quality),\n",
    "this is a strong result for a linear model."
